# 1 - Prerequisites (Inference Endpoint Setup for Sparse Embeddings)

- [ ]  Ensure you deploy Elastic's Trained Model **Elser**, for more information refer [here](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/machine-learning/current/ml-nlp-elser.html)
- [ ]  Ensure you deploy an **inference endpoint** named *hackathon*, why? Because this was born through Helios' participation in Elastic's **Hackathon for ElasticON 2025**, for more information refer [here](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/machine-learning/current/ml-nlp-elser.html); or run the action proceeding from this note

# 2 - Prerequisites (Index Templates)

- [ ]  Create `index template` for sparse embedding to converse with your data via AI Assistant (run action **Create Index Template Opendata-Chat**
- [ ]  You'd also want to create a separate `index template` for just the GeoJSON for map creation purposes (run action **Create Index Template Opendata Others**

# 3 - Kibana Objects

- [ ]  Download the `ndjson` object file named **opendata_maps.ndjson** from (here)[https://github.com/helios-solution/forge_the_future_hackathon_2025/blob/main/kibana_objects/opendata_maps.ndjson] then import it through your Kibana Saved Objects
